bug.short_desc: Update about window to use new background images

long_desc.thetext: Martell made some awesome new images for the about window, and this is where we will implement them!

Created attachment 524587 About Mockup
- revised background image mockup

Created attachment 524765 WIP patch
For this to work in RTL, I'll need horizontally flipped images. Sean, could you make those for me?

The once concern with that is with the current layout we'd axe the sun rising on the globe, the aurora.
could we simply change the justification and not the layout?

(In reply to comment #8) > could we simply change the justification and not the layout?
That will require more changes on my end, but I think that's a smarter choice. I'll do that.
Dark backgrounds of the about window look cool but do not match with the appearance of other programs on Windows including Firefox. Please give this a thought.
That's not a valid reason to not do it, a lot of software has custom about dialogs, especially on Windows. Consistency with the OS is a good point, where it matters.
These are special windows for special builds, at most only ~1% of our user base will ever see one of them.

I still need to test on Windows/Linux, but it looks good on OSX.
